(164,	2,	'2015-06-22 16:19:56',	'2015-06-22 20:19:56',	'Each year, more than 1,000 women gather at the “Girls Night Out” in August to support victims and survivors of domestic violence and their children. This year’s event will be from 6 to 10 p.m. on Aug. 15 at the state Culture Center. Since 1998, Girls Night Out has generated revenue to sustain the YWCA Charleston’s Resolve Family Abuse Program.\r\n\r\nAlong with the new venue, Girls Night Out each year features a novel theme voted on by the community. There are two themes this year. People can begin voting on the theme by visiting www.gnowv.com. The winning theme will be announced the evening of April 23 at the offices of Farmer Cline and Campbell.\r\n\r\nGirls Night Out sponsorships, hostess opportunities and tickets are available by contacting Carol Sun at 304-414-3113 or csun@ywcacharleston.org. Tickets are $125.',	'Girls Night Out - Supporting Victims of Domestic Violence',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'girls-night-out-supporting-victims-of-domestic-violence',	'',	'',	'2015-06-22 16:19:56',	'2015-06-22 20:19:56',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly&#038;p=164',	0,	'chronosly',	'',	0),
