(444,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:30:22',	'2015-07-01 16:30:22',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-287\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/festivall_pic-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"festivall_pic\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>FestivAll</h3>\r\nThe event features visual arts, music, theater, dance and film as well as other cultural and entertainment events. It mixes fine arts and pop arts in venues and locations all over Charleston and includes a wide variety of styles and genres.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long Charleston has lots to offer the City Explorer. There\'s always something to do in the area!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston’s diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Here’s a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Clay Center for the Arts and Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance Hall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Street</h3>\r\nThis bustling street serves as a main location for dining, learning and retail. Restaurants such as Ichiban, Pies and Pints, Adelphia, Graziano\'s Pizza and others line the streets, some offering outdoor dining.\r\n<h3>ArtWalk</h3>\r\nA free self-guided walking tour of Downtown Charleston\'s shops, galleries and businesses featuring a variety of art - from paintings and sculptures to  photography and music. ArtWalk is held the third Thursday of each month.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.artwalkcwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">artwalkcwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800’s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Soho’s restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Live on the Levee</h3>\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://liveontheleveecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">liveontheleveecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bridge Road Shops</h3>\r\nUnique shops located in a charming neighborhood commercial district. Experience world class dining, shop for your favorite designer clothes, decorate your home with the warmth of one-of-a kind accessories, and experience local and regional art.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.bridgeroad.org\" target=\"_blank\">bridgeroad.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hale Street</h3>\r\nThis hidden street gem offers a unique group of stores and restaurants. Shop at Stray Dog Antiques, get pampered at Tops Off Barber Shop, Salon and Spa, get a smoothie at Mission Savvy Vegan Cafe and dinner at Celsius.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>',	'City Explorer',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'187-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:30:22',	'2015-07-01 16:30:22',	'',	187,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/187-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(445,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:33:42',	'2015-07-01 16:33:42',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-297\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/shutterstock_173318291-300x191.jpg\" alt=\"BBall through hoop\" width=\"210\" height=\"134\" />\r\n<h3>Annual Charleston Public Courts Tennis Tournament</h3>\r\nJuly 10-18, 2015\r\n\r\nLargest annual tennis tournament in Charleston. The public courts tournament matches take place at Schoenbaum Tennis Complex, Tennis Indoor Center and Charleston Catholic High\r\nSchool Sports Complex. rain sites include tennis indoor center, YMCA and the Charleston Tennis Club.\r\n<h3>WVSSAC Tournaments</h3>\r\nThe West Virginia Secondary School Athletic Commission (WVSSAC) hold their annual high school boys basketball, girls basketball, volleyball, baseball, tennis and track and field state\r\ntournaments in the Charleston area throughout the year.\r\n\r\nBoys Basketball - March\r\nGirls Basketball - March\r\nVolleyball - November\r\nBaseball - June\r\nTennis - April\r\nTrack and Field - April\r\n<h3>Sportsfest Meets WV Games</h3>\r\nSportsFEST includes the Jet Ski Hyrdo-Turf National Championship and the EVP Pro Am Beach Championship. WV Games, the largest collection of sanctioned sporting events in West Virginia, includes events such as a cornhole tournament, crossfit, tabata bootcamp, slalom skateboarding, wrestling, Jiu Jitsu and the West Virginia Storm will be stunting and tumbling. In total, more than 400 professional athletes will compete this weekend.\r\n<h3>Capital City Challenge</h3>\r\nSeptember 19, 2015\r\n\r\n4.2 mile Run, 4.2 mile Row, 16.8 mile Ride\r\n\r\nRun, Row &amp; Ride through the capital city on this flat, fast course that showcases the beauty of downtown Charleston. This unique yet competitive event is designed for competitors of all fitness and skill levels. This family-friendly challenge features a post-race picnic with music, 