(451,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:41:46',	'2015-07-01 16:41:46',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Adrenaline Junkies</h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-240\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/volleyball4-300x177.jpg\" alt=\"volleyball4\" width=\"210\" height=\"124\" />\r\n<h3>WV Games/Sportsfest</h3>\r\nCome out and enjoy jet ski racing, professional volleyball and tons more during this fun-filled weekend. The \"Governors\' Cup\" is the final stop of the Hydro-Turf Pro Watercross Tour, where\r\nthe pro riders who have been traveling the tour will be crowned the U.S.A. National Champions. Amateur, Novice and Junior competitors will also be vying for the National Amateur Championship title. For more information on the National Championship Pro Watercross Tour.\r\n<h3>Bridge Day</h3>\r\nBridge Day, one of the largest extreme sports event in the world, is held annually on the third Saturday in October in Fayette County, West Virginia (WV). Hundreds of BASE jumpers and nearly 80,000 spectators are expected to attend the event. Vendor booths and food are available on the bridge, along with the best overlook of the New River Gorge.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nFall is a great time to catch some great (and unique) events for adrenaline junkies.  September and October offer good weather but not hot conditions.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Climb zip, row and ride through the Charleston West Virginia area with these great heart-pumping activities.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Adventures on the Gorge</h3>\r\nAOTG offers a variety of adrenaline pumping adventures including whitewater rafting on the New and Gauley Rivers, canopy tours, zip lines, guided hiking, paintball, caving, horseback riding and more! With restaurants and kids camps, the whole family can really make a day of it!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">219 Chestnutburg Rd.\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\n<a href=\"http://www.adventuresonthegorge.com\" target=\"_blank\">adventuresonthegorge.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hatfield and McCoy Trails</h3>\r\nEight trail systems stretch over 700 total miles of West Virginia allowing UTV, ATV, dirt bike riders with a world-class trail system. All trails are open 365 days a year and new trails are constantly being added.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">28 Big Pinnacle Branch Rd.\r\nJulian, WV 25529\r\n<a href=\"http://www.trailsheaven.com\" target=\"_blank\">trailsheaven.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>eNeRGy Rock Climbing Gym</h3>\r\nIndoor Rock Climbing Gym providing opportunities for beginners through experts to climb in the Charleston area. The gym features 16 ft tall 5, 10 and 15 degree overhanging walls, 14 ft tall 30\r\ndegree overhanging wall, a cave with 45, 60 and horizontal roof features/. The cave also has a 14 ft long hand crack that splits and an overhanging arete. In the loft area, there is a 13 ft tall 50 degree wall that is perfect for training. There is also a 13 ft tall \'wave\' wall for transitional angle training and a mushroom wall to practice mantling and topping out. Shoes available for rental and day passes (5-9pm) available for $12. No additional equipment needed prior to entry.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">269 Graham Dr.\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n<a href=\"http://www.energyrockgym.com/\" target=\"_blank\">energyrockgym.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Hidden Trails Motorsports</h3>\r\nHidden Trails Motorsports sell new and used motorsports vehicles with brands including Can-Am, Sea-Doo, Spyder, Suzuki and all Yamaha brands. They also service and have parts available for the brands listed as well as powersports brands including Polaris, Kawasaki, Arctic Cat and Honda.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">3014 E Dupont Ave.\r\nBelle, WV 25015\r\n<a href=\"http://www.hiddentrailsmoto.com/\" target=\"_blank\">hiddentrailsmoto.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>BridgeWalk</h3>\r\nTake a walk along the bottom of the New River Gorge Bridge! This 2-3 hour tour will take guests from the Canyon Rim Visitor Center across the 3030 foot length of the bridge and then shuttle back to the center. The catwalk has been an existing structure of the bridge since its original construction, and Bridge Walk LLC saw an opportunity to give unique tours across the walkway. Creating Bridge Walk only required a simple shuttle system, improving the trail access, and installing an innovative safety system for guests making it impossible for tour guests to fall off the bridge.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Canyon Rim Visitor Center\r\n162 Visitor Center Rd.\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\n<a href=\"http://bridgewalk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Bridgewalk.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- end of col-container-cb -->',	'Adrenaline Junkie',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'206-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:41:46',	'2015-07-01 16:41:46',	'',	206,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/206-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(452,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:43:08',	'2015-07-01 16:43:08',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/server1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-347\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/server1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"server1\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a>\r\n<h3>Fest of Ale</h3>\r\nThe Charleston area\'s original beer tasting event. Held at the Comedy Zone, participants sample 10-12 beers along with food pairings. Entertainment provided by the Comedy Zone. Some wine offerings are available in place of beer for those who want to try something different.\r\n<h3>Blues, Brews and BBQ</h3>\r\nPart of FestivAll, Charleston’s Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party. Beer and BBQ vendors provide suds and great food while blues musicians take the stage and attendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nFall is a great time for beer tastings and other events that celebrate the brew...plus Oktoberfest beers are coming out! Enjoy beer year-round at local restaurants as well.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>The beer is flowing in the capitol city. With new laws in WV allowing growlers to be purchased at Charleston establishments and bars, the craft beer craze is even stronger in the Mountain State.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Charleston Brewing Company</h3>\r\nA micro-brewery attached to Black Sheep Burritos in the heart of downtown Charleston. Fine craft beers of all styles brewed and served on-site.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">702 Quarrier St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.charlestonbrewingcompany.com\" target=\"_blank\">charlestonbrewingcompany.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Pies and Pints</h3>\r\nPies &amp; Pints restaurant in Charleston West Virginia serves unique, delicious gourmet pizza and craft beer in the center of the city\'s downtown shopping district.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">222 Capitol Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://piesandpints.net/\" target=\"_blank\">piesandpints.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bricks and Barrels</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for something different, Bricks and Barrels is a great option! Sit in one of the Barrel shaped booths and enjoy their large variety of beers and wines and food from their eclectic menu.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1214 Smith St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bricksnbarrels.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.bricksnbarrels.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>The Wine &amp; Cheese Shop</h3>\r\nLocated at the Capitol Market, the shop features a huge selection of wine, cheese, craft beer, gift items, accessories, and glassware.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/merchants/wine-cheese-shop\" target=\"_blank\">Wine+Cheese-Shop</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>B&amp;D Gastropub</h3>\r\nThe extensive menu includes appetizers such as jerk chicken nachos &amp; feta and dates wrapped in bacon. The menu will also offers burgers, including stuffed patties, fresh-cut chips and salads.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">200 35th St SE #1\r\nCharleston, WV 25304\r\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/BandDGastropub\">facebook.com/BanDGastropub</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Copper Pint Pub</h3>\r\nCopper Pint Pub is an Irish Pub with a large selection of local and imported craft beers. Also carry a huge selection of Irish Whiskeys, Bourbons and Scotches to satisfy the most diverse taste buds.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">808 Kanawha Blvd., E\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CopperPintPub\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/CopperPintPub</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/BrewEnthusiast-Tour-map.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-428\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/BrewEnthusiast-Tour-map-300x198.jpg\" alt=\"BrewEnthusiast Tour map\" width=\"460\" height=\"303\" /></a> </div>\r\n\r\n</div>',	'Brew Enthusiast',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'198-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:43:08',	'2015-07-01 16:43:08',	'',	198,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/198-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(453,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:44:35',	'2015-07-01 16:44:35',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-287\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/festivall_pic-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"festivall_pic\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>FestivAll</h3>\r\nThe event features visual arts, music, theater, dance and film as well as other cultural and entertainment events. It mixes fine arts and pop arts in venues and locations all over Charleston and includes a wide variety of styles and genres.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long Charleston has lots to offer the City Explorer. There\'s always something to do in the area!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston’s diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Here’s a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Clay Center for the Arts and Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance Hall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Street</h3>\r\nThis bustling street serves as a main location for dining, learning and retail. Restaurants such as Ichiban, Pies and Pints, Adelphia, Graziano\'s Pizza and others line the streets, some offering outdoor dining.\r\n<h3>ArtWalk</h3>\r\nA free self-guided walking tour of Downtown Charleston\'s shops, galleries and businesses featuring a variety of art - from paintings and sculptures to  photography and music. ArtWalk is held the third Thursday of each month.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.artwalkcwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">artwalkcwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800’s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Soho’s restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Live on the Levee</h3>\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://liveontheleveecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">liveontheleveecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bridge Road Shops</h3>\r\nUnique shops located in a charming neighborhood commercial district. Experience world class dining, shop for your favorite designer clothes, decorate your home with the warmth of one-of-a kind accessories, and experience local and regional art.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.bridgeroad.org\" target=\"_blank\">bridgeroad.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hale Street</h3>\r\nThis hidden street gem offers a unique group of stores and restaurants. Shop at Stray Dog Antiques, get pampered at Tops Off Barber Shop, Salon and Spa, get a smoothie at Mission Savvy Vegan Cafe and dinner at Celsius.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>',	'City Explorer',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'187-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:44:35',	'2015-07-01 16:44:35',	'',	187,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/187-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(454,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:44:48',	'2015-07-01 16:44:48',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Families</h4>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a>\r\n<h3>Clay Center Family Fun Days</h3>\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n<h3>Children\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair</h3>\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n<h3>Movie Nights at Magic Island</h3>\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, there’s never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha County Public Library\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://kanawhalibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhalibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">South Charleston Public Library\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">southcharlestonlibrary.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Chuck E Cheese</h3>\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheese’s is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chuckecheese.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Clay Center for the Arts and Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WV’s only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and\r\nattractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:44:48',	'2015-07-01 16:44:48',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(455,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:46:02',	'2015-07-01 16:46:02',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-360\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/taste_of_all1-300x230.jpg\" alt=\"taste_of_all1\" width=\"210\" height=\"161\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>Smoke on the Water Chili Cookoff</h3>\r\nChili cooks compete to see who has the best red, green and home-style chili and salsa. Kids activities, frozen t-shirt and hot pepper eating contests, live music, local food vendors and plenty of cold drinks. Proceeds benefit HospiceCare.\r\n<h3>Mac and Cheese Cookoff</h3>\r\nMac and Cheese enthusiasts enter and taste the Charleston area\'s best Macaroni and Cheese. Proceeds benefit the Childhood Language Center of Charleston, WV.\r\n<h3>Taste-of-All</h3>\r\nTaste-of-All Charleston is a tour of the culinary talents and amazing cuisine available throughout Charleston, WV. Fun for the whole family, visitors can taste amazing dishes served by some of\r\nthe gifted chefs and restaurants from the valley.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nSpring, summer and fall are perfect for outdoor dining but all year-round is great for those special Charleston places that love to serve you!\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>You don’t have to look very far to find great cuisine in Charleston! We have highlighted just a few of the amazing places you can go to have a casual meal, a quick bite, a fancy feast or make your own!</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Bluegrass Kitchen</h3>\r\nFarm-to-table comfort food with a modern edge. Specialties are vegetarian &amp; omnivorous dishes made from ingredients naturally sourced within WV and the Appalachians served in a dining room restored to its circa 1920\'s beauty.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1600 Washington St E\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bluegrasswv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bluegrasswv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Charleston Bread Company</h3>\r\n​Breads, cookies, pastries and more baked fresh every day.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">601 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, West Virginia 25301</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Block</h3>\r\nThe Block offers cocktails and small bites complimented by views of downtown Capitol St. The restaurant features an active cheese cave and glass enclosed wine cellar. Jazz music on selected nights.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">201 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theblockwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">theblockwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800’s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Soho’s restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>J.Q. Dickenson Salt Works</h3>\r\nDescendants of the original salt makers in the Kanawha Valley produce clean, artisinal salt, harvested by hand. Tours are available with reservations.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">371 Kanawha Salines Dr.\r\nMalden, WV 25306\r\n<a href=\"http://www.jqdsalt.com/\" target=\"_blank\">jqdsalt.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Black Sheep Burritos</h3>\r\nLocated in the heart of downtown, Black Sheep offers an eclectic mix of tex-mex menu items and Charleston Brewing Company beer. One of the best brunch menus in the Kanawha Valley.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">702 Quarrier St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blacksheepwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blacksheepwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ellen’s Ice Cream</h3>\r\nEllen’s Homemade Ice Cream was born over 15 years ago with the simple mission to delight customers with all-natural, high-quality ingredients and a welcoming and comfortable atmosphere.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">225 Capitol St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://ellensicecream.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ellensicecream.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>West Side Farmer’s Market</h3>\r\nThe purpose and mission of the market is to educate about local food resources and to revitalize the community by creating a vibrant market at which local farmers and home gardeners may sell their produce.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">303 Washington St. West\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n<a href=\"http://wsfmcharleston.com/\" target=\"_blank\">wsfmcharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Butter It Up!</h3>\r\nEver had butter in your coffee? This is a must-try. Butter it up! is a gluten free coffee shop. They offer paleoish breakfast, lunch, and dinner options in addition to local products.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">714 Virginia St E,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/butteritupcrw\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/butteritupcrw</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>',	'Foodie',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'189-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:46:02',	'2015-07-01 16:46:02',	'',	189,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/189-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(456,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:47:24',	'2015-07-01 16:47:24',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-367\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/capitol_night_-shutter-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"capitol_night_-shutter (1)\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>Battle of Scary Creek/Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge - Civil War Reenactment</h3>\r\nPart of a Civil War weekend in Hurricane, the event commemorates two engagements of the Civil War separated by a space of two years. The Battle of Scary Creek., July 17, 1861 and the Blue and Gray Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge, March 28, 1863. Also, enjoy crafts, sutler\'s row, storytelling, a night firing, parade drills, a ladies tea, a historical lantern tour and a military dance.\r\n<h3>WV Day Celebrations</h3>\r\nCelebrate West Virginia\'s birthday with a variety of activities on the grounds of the WV State Capitol.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nHistory is happening every day of the year and this is certainly the case for those wanting to learn more about Charleston and West Virginia\'s history.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston’s diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Here’s a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>WV State Museum</h3>\r\nThis free-to-the-pubic museum offers an interactive look into the history, culture and treasures of West Virginia. The museum is designed as a timeline telling story of WV. A museum gift shop offers WV locally-made products.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">WV Division of Culture and History\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvculture.org/museum/State-Museum-Index.html\" target=\"_blank\">WV-State-Museum</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WV Humanities Council</h3>\r\nThe Council provides constant events and programs promoting the Mountain State and it\'s art, literature and history. It is located at the MacFarland-Hubbard House, which is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1310 Kanawha Blvd., E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvhumanities.org/\" target=\"_blank\">wvhumanities.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Malden</h3>\r\nHistoric town just east of Charleston. VIsit Booker T. Washington\'s childhood home, African Zion Baptist Church, J.Q. Dickenson Salt and many other historic buildings and sites.\r\n<h3>Governor’s Mansion</h3>\r\nTours of the Governor\'s Mansion begin on the front porch of the Mansion on Thursdays and Fridays. Reservations are required and are honored on a first-come, first-serve basis. Call for reservations at 304-558-4839.\r\n<h3>West Virginia State Capitol</h3>\r\nTours begin on the first floor Rotunda. Groups under 10 are welcome to join a regularly scheduled tour without reservations. Groups of more than 10 are best served with a reservation and tours of Senate/Representatives chamber require reservations. 304-558-2601\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Craik-Patton House</h3>\r\nCraik-Patton House was built about 1834 in the Greek Revival style. It is open for tours from April through October. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1970.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2809 Kanawha Blvd. E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.craik-patton.org/\" target=\"_blank\">craik-patton.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Coal Heritage Trail</h3>\r\nA driving trail that winds through over 187 rugged miles of scenic industrial heritage. You will pass through National Historic Districts and the physical remnants of the coal boom such as coal miners\' homes, company stores, company offices and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">100 Kelly Avenue\r\nOak Hill, WV 25901\r\n<a href=\"http://www.coalheritage.org\" target=\"_blank\">coalheritage.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Blenko Glass</h3>\r\nFor over 100 years, Blenko has maintained the tradition of hand making glassware in America. They offer a wide range of products which include functional glassware, art glass, mouth blown sheet glass, dalle de verre and other quality products. Tours are available.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">9 Bill Blenko Drive\r\nMilton, WV 25541\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blenko.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blenko.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Kanawha Blvd. Historical Markers</h3>\r\nAs you stroll along the riverbank, you will come across a series of historic markers commemorating moments in West Virginia history. These markers are part of the over 1,000 markers throughout the state marking sites of significance.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>',	'History Buff',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'191-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:47:24',	'2015-07-01 16:47:24',	'',	191,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/191-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(457,	3,	'2015-07-01 12:50:45',	'2015-07-01 16:50:45',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-367\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/capitol_night_-shutter-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"capitol_night_-shutter (1)\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>Battle of Scary Creek/Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge - Civil War Reenactment</h3>\r\nPart of a Civil War weekend in Hurricane, the event commemorates two engagements of the Civil War separated by a space of two years. The Battle of Scary Creek., July 17, 1861 and the Blue and Gray Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge, March 28, 1863. Also, enjoy crafts, sutler\'s row, storytelling, a night firing, parade drills, a ladies tea, a historical lantern tour and a military dance.\r\n<h3>WV Day Celebrations</h3>\r\nCelebrate West Virginia\'s birthday with a variety of activities on the grounds of the WV State Capitol.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nHistory is happening every day of the year and this is certainly the case for those wanting to learn more about Charleston and West Virginia\'s history.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston’s diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Here’s a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>WV State Museum</h3>\r\nThis free-to-the-public museum offers an interactive look into the history, culture and treasures of West Virginia. The museum is designed as a timeline telling story of WV. A museum gift shop offers WV locally-made products.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">WV Division of Culture and History\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvculture.org/museum/State-Museum-Index.html\" target=\"_blank\">WV-State-Museum</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WV Humanities Council</h3>\r\nThe Council provides constant events and programs promoting the Mountain State and it\'s art, literature and history. It is located at the MacFarland-Hubbard House, which is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1310 Kanawha Blvd., E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvhumanities.org/\" target=\"_blank\">wvhumanities.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Malden</h3>\r\nHistoric town just east of Charleston. VIsit Booker T. Washington\'s childhood home, African Zion Baptist Church, J.Q. Dickenson Salt and many other historic buildings and sites.\r\n<h3>Governor’s Mansion</h3>\r\nTours of the Governor\'s Mansion begin on the front porch of the Mansion on Thursdays and Fridays. Reservations are required and are honored on a first-come, first-serve basis. Call for reservations at 304-558-4839.\r\n<h3>West Virginia State Capitol</h3>\r\nTours begin on the first floor Rotunda. Groups under 10 are welcome to join a regularly scheduled tour without reservations. Groups of more than 10 are best served with a reservation and tours of Senate/Representatives chamber require reservations. 304-558-2601\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Craik-Patton House</h3>\r\nCraik-Patton House was built about 1834 in the Greek Revival style. It is open for tours from April through October. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1970.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2809 Kanawha Blvd. E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.craik-patton.org/\" target=\"_blank\">craik-patton.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Coal Heritage Trail</h3>\r\nA driving trail that winds through over 187 rugged miles of scenic industrial heritage. You will pass through National Historic Districts and the physical remnants of the coal boom such as coal miners\' homes, company stores, company offices and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">100 Kelly Avenue\r\nOak Hill, WV 25901\r\n<a href=\"http://www.coalheritage.org\" target=\"_blank\">coalheritage.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Blenko Glass</h3>\r\nFor over 100 years, Blenko has maintained the tradition of hand making glassware in America. They offer a wide range of products which include functional glassware, art glass, mouth blown sheet glass, dalle de verre and other quality products. Tours are available.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">9 Bill Blenko Drive\r\nMilton, WV 25541\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blenko.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blenko.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Kanawha Blvd. Historical Markers</h3>\r\nAs you stroll along the riverbank, you will come across a series of historic markers commemorating moments in West Virginia history. These markers are part of the over 1,000 markers throughout the state marking sites of significance.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>',	'History Buff',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'191-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 12:50:45',	'2015-07-01 16:50:45',	'',	191,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/191-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(458,	3,	'2015-07-01 13:07:40',	'2015-07-01 17:07:40',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-294 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/live_on_levee1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"live_on_levee1\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />\r\n<h3>Live On The Levee</h3>\r\nOutdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<h3>East End Pub Crawl</h3>\r\nJoin in on the St. Patrick\'s Day fun on the East End of Charleston.  Live, local Celtic music from FOOTMAD, walk from bar to bar (over 10) enjoying drink specials and look for the hidden shamrocks throughout the area in order to win big!\r\n<h3>Boo Bash</h3>\r\nAll the ghosts and goblins come out to play at this traditional-style Halloween party.  Dance the night away with the event\'s DJ and enjoy great food and drinks, games and a photo booth. Hosted by the South Charleston Chamber of Commerce, its a fun-filled fright night!\r\n<h3>HallowEast</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for a spooky time, HallowEast has lots of events to make your Halloween. ArtMares, Main Street Murder Mystery, East End Zombie Walk, Run Like Hell Zombie 5K and the Costume Crawl are all exciting events that make this week of scary a truly ghouly experience.\r\n<h3>Murder Mysteries</h3>\r\nThese exciting Who-Dun-It events are sure to entertain the best of detectives.  Located at the Comedy Zone in the Holiday Inn &amp; Suites, participants enjoy a buffet dinner and an entertaining interactive show with a different theme each time.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nThere\'s always time to party!  But if you\'re looking for great times with special events, look around the holidays...particularly St. Patty\'s Day and  Halloween!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Whether you want fast-paced excitement, great music or a low-key culinary experience, there’s always something to do late-night in Charleston!</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Comedy Zone</h3>\r\nTwo of the nation\'s funniest comedians travel to Charleston to entertain the crowds. Full food and drink menus available during the show. Shows are Fridays at 8pm &amp; Saturdays at 7pm and 9pm.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">400 2nd Ave.\r\nCharleston, WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://comedyzonecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">comedyzonecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Street Nightlife</h3>\r\nCapitol Street &amp; adjacent Kanawha Blvd. have a variety of bars/lounges for all scenes. Whether you’re looking for a great glass of wine, sports bar, irish pub or game of pool, it’s all here!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bricks and Barrels</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for an upscale evening, Bricks and Barrels is the place. Sit in one of the Barrel shaped booths and enjoy their large variety of beers and wines along with their eclectic menu.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1214 Smith St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bricksnbarrels.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bricksnbarrels.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Empty Glass</h3>\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charleston’s historically diverse East End. Here you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">410 Elizabeth St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.emptyglass.com\" target=\"_blank\">emptyglass.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Celsius</h3>\r\nAn upscale lounge serving wine, craft beers and specialty cocktails. The food menu includes burgers, salads, flat breads and a unique variety of dishes.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">212 Hale St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CelsiusWV\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/CelsiusWV</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Timothy\'s</h3>\r\nTimothy’s is located directly below the Quarrier Diner. Watch your favorite sports on any one of the 17 high definition flat screens. They are constantly hosting events from live music, trivia nights and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1022 Quarrier St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.timothyssportsbar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">timothyssportsbar.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mardi Gras Casino</h3>\r\nOver 90,000 square feet of gaming space, the Mardi Gras Casino offers over 30 table games, over 1,000 slot machines, greyhound racing, restaurants and bars and much more!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">#1 Greyhound Drive\r\nCross Lanes, WV 25313\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mardigrascasinowv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">mardigrascasinowv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>',	'Night Owl',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'200-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-01 13:07:40',	'2015-07-01 17:07:40',	'',	200,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/200-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
