(1413,	3,	'2015-08-17 14:39:59',	'2015-08-17 18:39:59',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_287\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"210\"]<img class=\"wp-image-287\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/festivall_pic-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"festivall_pic\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /> Directional Signs from FestivAll[/caption]\r\n<h3>FestivAll</h3>\r\nThe event features visual arts, music, theater, dance and film as well as other cultural and entertainment events. It mixes fine arts and pop arts in venues and locations all over Charleston and includes a wide variety of styles and genres.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long Charleston has lots to offer the City Explorer. There\'s always something to do in the area!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston’s diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Here’s a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1212 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_A.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Clay Center for the Arts and       Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance Hall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1246 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-C.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Capitol Street</h3>\r\nThis bustling street serves as a main location for dining, learning and retail. Restaurants such as Ichiban, Pies and Pints, Adelphia, Graziano\'s Pizza and others line the streets, some offering outdoor dining.\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1244 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-E.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />ArtWalk</h3>\r\nA free self-guided walking tour of Downtown Charleston\'s shops, galleries and businesses featuring a variety of art - from paintings and sculptures to  photography and music. ArtWalk is held the third Thursday of each month.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.artwalkcwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">artwalkcwv.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1242 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-G.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800’s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Soho’s restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img cla